From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 05:40:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] external: use system Boost for non-Android builds

The ext-boost submodule URL used by this EKA2L1 revision is no longer
available anonymously. Linux builds do not need the Android-only
interface target that points at that submodule, and Dynarmic can use the
Buildroot-provided Boost package.

Keep the existing ext-boost path only for Android builds and avoid
poisoning Boost_INCLUDE_DIR for normal Linux builds.

Signed-off-by: suckbluefrog <suckbluefrog@proton.me>
---
 src/external/CMakeLists.txt | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/external/CMakeLists.txt b/src/external/CMakeLists.txt
index fb932f95..c4efa2b3 100644
--- a/src/external/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/external/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -4,9 +4,9 @@ include(CheckSymbolExists)
 add_library(miniz miniz/miniz.h miniz/miniz.c)
 target_include_directories(miniz PUBLIC miniz)
 
-# Force Boost directory for Dynarmic - we never use one
-set (Boost_INCLUDE_DIR "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/ext-boost/" CACHE PATH "Boost include directory")
 if (ANDROID)
+    # Force Boost directory for Dynarmic - we never use one
+    set (Boost_INCLUDE_DIR "${CMAKE_CURRENT_SOURCE_DIR}/ext-boost/" CACHE PATH "Boost include directory")
     add_definitions(-DBOOST_ERROR_CODE_HEADER_ONLY
             -DBOOST_SYSTEM_NO_LIB
             -DBOOST_DATE_TIME_NO_LIB
-- 
2.43.0
